Triangle $QRS$ has base 4 and height $b - 4$.  Triangle $QOP$ has base $b$ and height $b$, so the ratio of their areas is
\[\frac{[QRS]}{[QOP]} = \frac{(b - 4) \cdot 2}{b \cdot \frac{b}{2}} = \frac{4(b - 4)}{b^2}.\]We are given that this ratio is $9/25,$ so
